sentence: On Monday analysts at Bank of America/Merrill Lynch said that they now see shares of The Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ) reaching $72.
The home improvement retailer is well positioned to benefit from a housing market recovery according the the BOA/ML analysts.
The $72 expected share price is a $12.44, or 21%, increase from Friday's closing share price of $59.56.
Bank of America/Merrill Lynch gives Home Depot a "Buy" rating.
The share price for Home Depot was flat in premarket trading on Monday.
The home improvement giant's shares are up 42% YTD.
Shares of Home Depot ( HD ) have a 1.95% dividend yield, based on Friday's closing stock price of $59.56.
The stock has technical support in the $56 price area.
If the shares can firm up, we see overhead resistance around the $62-$63 price levels.
